It's 9.9 yuan for two cupcakes.

88
00:06:58,765 --> 00:07:02,915
Free delivery in the city. Limited supply. We're putting out the link, okay?

89
00:07:02,915 --> 00:07:04,935
Click on the link.

90
00:07:04,935 --> 00:07:09,435
- All right, let's call it a day. Share the meeting minutes. 
 - Okay.

91
00:07:09,435 --> 00:07:13,715
Get ready for the Product Insourcing Conference this afternoon.

92
00:07:14,735 --> 00:07:16,335
Lin Tuo, join the meeting.

93
00:07:16,335 --> 00:07:19,275
- Yes. 
 - Chief Designer.

94
00:07:20,675 --> 00:07:22,575
What is that?

95
00:07:22,575 --> 00:07:26,075
We hold an interior bidding every month.

96
00:07:26,075 --> 00:07:28,675
Each team shows their new products to be rated.

97
00:07:28,675 --> 00:07:32,035
The one with the highest score will be put into production.

98
00:07:32,035 --> 00:07:36,395
Even I haven't been invited yet. Good for you.

99
00:07:51,575 --> 00:07:53,955
- Xiao Tuo. 
  - Xiao Que. 

100
00:07:53,955 --> 00:07:57,975
I'm finally attending a meeting of the design department. And it's quite a serious meeting.

101
00:07:57,975 --> 00:08:01,395
Way to go. What are you going to do?

102
00:08:01,395 --> 00:08:06,115
I don't have any design to demonstrate. I'm just there to learn. And I get to vote.

103
00:08:06,115 --> 00:08:10,175
Someone is not upset anymore. Look how excited you are.

104
00:08:10,175 --> 00:08:13,475
- What are you doing? 
 -  I was just about to tell you. 

105
00:08:13,475 --> 00:08:19,775
He Xindi sold all my cakes and cookies on the livestreaming without even telling me.

106
00:08:19,775 --> 00:08:22,675
- So sudden? 
 -  Exactly. 

107
00:08:22,675 --> 00:08:28,355
Everybody loved the cakes and cookies.

108
00:08:28,355 --> 00:08:30,355
 So she started selling them. 

109
00:08:30,355 --> 00:08:32,795
It's more than reasonable to make profits.

110
00:08:32,795 --> 00:08:36,815
You like it in the first place. It's good that you can make money.

111
00:08:36,815 --> 00:08:39,674
It just caught me off guard.

112
00:08:39,674 --> 00:08:41,955
You're a genius duck driven onto the perch.

113
00:08:41,955 --> 00:08:44,415
I'm not a duck.

114
00:08:47,655 --> 00:08:50,375
- I have work to do. Talk later. 
 -  Okay. 

115
00:08:50,375 --> 00:08:51,575
Good luck. Love you.

116
00:08:51,575 --> 00:08:54,316
Love you, bye. 
    

117
00:08:55,955 --> 00:09:01,615
I hope you can form constructive ideas about every project and product.

118
00:09:01,615 --> 00:09:06,175
This is not a conference to flatter each other.

119
00:09:06,175 --> 00:09:09,075
Let's be honest and straightforward.

120
00:09:09,075 --> 00:09:13,695
I find these projects mediocre.

121
00:09:14,595 --> 00:09:18,955
Junyi, I know you're working on the factory line.

122
00:09:18,955 --> 00:09:21,595
But we don't want cheap furniture.

123
00:09:21,595 --> 00:09:26,115
How do we call it a "Ji Jia Design" if there is no design?

124
00:09:26,115 --> 00:09:29,475
I'm rejecting all these proposals.

125
00:09:29,475 --> 00:09:32,075
Hand in new ones in a week.

126
00:09:32,075 --> 00:09:36,455
Next, Wei Haiyang.

127
00:09:38,575 --> 00:09:43,400
Okay, I'll present our design and proposal on behalf of our team. 
    

128
00:09:43,400 --> 00:09:44,910
   

129
00:09:44,910 --> 00:09:48,595
It's just a checkup. Why did you come with me?

130
00:09:48,595 --> 00:09:51,795
It's your first time here. You may be confused.

131
00:09:51,795 --> 00:09:55,455
Why would I be confused? I'm not silly.

132
00:09:55,455 --> 00:09:58,975
Well, I'm here. So stop nagging me.

133
00:10:01,335 --> 00:10:03,215
Look at that kid.

134
00:10:05,255 --> 00:10:06,755
What happened to him?

135
00:10:06,755 --> 00:10:09,635
His legs look fine. Why is he in a wheelchair?

136
00:10:09,635 --> 00:10:11,955
Is he paralyzed?

137
00:10:11,955 --> 00:10:13,495
Mind your own business.

138
00:10:13,495 --> 00:10:18,475
Look at him. He's so young. It's a pity to be paralyzed.

139
00:10:18,475 --> 00:10:20,815
How is he going to live?

140
00:10:22,395 --> 00:10:26,855
- If I get paralyzed in bed one day, just give up on me. 
 - Don't jinx it.

141
00:10:26,855 --> 00:10:30,415
Seriously, I'm not going to have all the tubes on me.

142
00:10:30,415 --> 00:10:33,915
- Why waste the money? Seriously. 
 - Don't talk nonsense.

143
00:10:33,915 --> 00:10:38,795
 No. 39 An Hegui, please visit Internal Medicine Consultation Room 1. 

144
00:10:38,795 --> 00:10:42,935
That's our proposal. The mass production won't be a problem.

145
00:10:42,935 --> 00:10:45,655
- Thank you. 
 - Sit.

146
00:10:49,435 --> 00:10:52,155
Any thoughts?

147
00:10:52,155 --> 00:10:56,075
Let's hear from the new people.

148
00:10:56,075 --> 00:10:58,775
I'd like some new perspectives.

149
00:11:00,155 --> 00:11:02,070
Lin Tuo.

150
00:11:03,020 --> 00:11:05,535
You've been here for a while.

151
00:11:05,535 --> 00:11:09,935
It's your first time in this meeting. What do you think?

152
00:11:12,315 --> 00:11:15,715
It's pretty cool.

153
00:11:17,515 --> 00:11:21,415
We want your ideas, not comments.

154
00:11:21,415 --> 00:11:24,335
Tell us the pros and cons.

155
00:11:38,500 --> 00:11:43,300
Wei Haiyang, have you been intimidating him?

156
00:11:43,300 --> 00:11:45,300
He's too scared to talk.

157
00:11:46,300 --> 00:11:48,030
Go ahead.

158
00:11:49,230 --> 00:11:51,500
Aren't you quite eloquent?

159
00:11:53,900 --> 00:11:57,900
All right, then I'll express my opinion.

160
00:11:57,900 --> 00:12:02,000
This series features a special design

161
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:06,000
that adopts a light luxury style with European court elements.

162
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:10,300
It's gorgeous and vintage. But it's too complicated.

163
00:12:10,300 --> 00:12:13,100
And takes up too much space. It's not practical.

164
00:12:13,100 --> 00:12:18,900
So there will be wasted raw material. The cost may multiply because of that.

165
00:12:18,900 --> 00:12:22,900
Plus, such a design suits big houses better.

166
00:12:22,900 --> 00:12:26,100
It sets the bar high for the buyers.

167
00:12:40,300 --> 00:12:46,300
That's just my point of view.

168
00:12:46,300 --> 00:12:47,900
Sit.

169
00:12:51,500 --> 00:12:58,100
All right. Good. I agree.

170
00:12:58,100 --> 00:13:02,600
We want honest opinions throughout the conference.

171
00:13:03,275 --> 00:13:05,495
Who's next?

172
00:13:11,400 --> 00:13:14,500
Come on, that's not your report.

173
00:13:16,300 --> 00:13:20,200
You're fine. Just pay attention to your diet.

174
00:13:20,200 --> 00:13:22,700
I scheduled your next appointment here.

175
00:13:22,700 --> 00:13:25,500
Come whenever you feel something wrong.

176
00:13:25,500 --> 00:13:27,200
Okay.

177
00:13:27,200 --> 00:13:32,100
Doctor. My dad doesn't sleep well. He has sleep apnea.

178
00:13:32,100 --> 00:13:34,500
Sometimes.

179
00:13:34,500 --> 00:13:37,100
I'll prescribe you some medicine.

180
00:13:37,100 --> 00:13:39,400
Measure your blood pressure every day.

181
00:13:39,400 --> 00:13:43,800
Okay, that's it for today. Dismiss.

182
00:13:44,435 --> 00:13:47,195
Junyi, come with me.

183
00:14:02,500 --> 00:14:04,400
Director Wei.

184
00:14:08,600 --> 00:14:11,300
Please express yourself next time.

185
00:14:11,300 --> 00:14:14,900
Don't make the kid who's on probation do it for you.

186
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:20,400
What a great apprentice.

187
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:31,850
All right.

188
00:14:33,150 --> 00:14:35,600
You're really bold.

189
00:14:42,700 --> 00:14:45,200
He's your junior?

190
00:14:45,900 --> 00:14:47,600
You recommended him here?

191
00:14:47,600 --> 00:14:49,100
Yeah.

192
00:14:51,600 --> 00:14:54,300
You picked a good one.

193
00:14:54,300 --> 00:14:57,700
He's new and doesn't know how to speak.

194
00:14:57,700 --> 00:14:59,700
You won't be mad at him, right?

195
00:14:59,700 --> 00:15:02,000
Do I look so petty to you?

196
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:03,900
Of course not.

197
00:15:18,300 --> 00:15:20,000
Come in.

198
00:15:24,100 --> 00:15:25,800
Yes?

199
00:15:28,055 --> 00:15:34,095
I'd like to apologize. I didn't mean to cause trouble.

200
00:15:34,895 --> 00:15:38,700
What's done is done. Why bother apologizing?

201
00:15:38,700 --> 00:15:44,200
I didn't expect that Director Han would blame it on you.

202
00:15:44,200 --> 00:15:48,300
- I... 
  - They believe I made you to say that, anyway.

203
00:15:48,300 --> 00:15:51,200
I took the blame. Why are you upset?

204
00:15:51,200 --> 00:15:55,100
I'm not upset. I can apologize to her.

205
00:15:55,100 --> 00:15:58,600
Don't cause me trouble, okay?

206
00:15:59,500 --> 00:16:01,400
Get back to work.

207
00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:16,800
   

208
00:16:24,100 --> 00:16:28,300
 Senior, did I offend Director Han? 

209
00:16:32,900 --> 00:16:37,400
 Don't be paranoid. I'm meeting a client. Talk later. 

210
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:42,300
Bad news. Director Han's design was rejected.

211
00:16:42,300 --> 00:16:44,700
I just heard from them.

212
00:17:08,500 --> 00:17:11,500
Is it that bad?

213
00:17:11,500 --> 00:17:14,000
It may be worse than imagined.

214
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:16,100
I don't think I'll make it through the probation.

215
00:17:16,100 --> 00:17:18,700
It may even end early.

216
00:17:18,700 --> 00:17:23,600
They're firing you just because you criticized their design?

217
00:17:25,200 --> 00:17:30,100
I asked HR. The directors get to rate my performance during the probation.

218
00:17:30,100 --> 00:17:32,900
You're not on her team. Why does she get to rate you?

219
00:17:32,900 --> 00:17:35,900
She's a director, after all. She's got the power.

220
00:17:35,900 --> 00:17:41,100
If she insists that I'm no good, will Chief Designer Wei stand up for me?

221
00:17:42,900 --> 00:17:47,700
Who's going to offend a colleague for a newcomer?

222
00:17:50,100 --> 00:17:53,300
I've been working so hard.

223
00:17:53,300 --> 00:17:57,900
There's finally hope. Now I'm doomed.

224
00:17:57,900 --> 00:18:01,800
What's wrong with me? Why would I say that?

225
00:18:01,800 --> 00:18:07,500
Why can't you speak the truth? It's so bad to hear the truth, huh?

226
00:18:07,500 --> 00:18:10,000
Such a person can be a director?

227
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:12,500
Well, she is a director.

228
00:18:14,300 --> 00:18:17,900
Fine, whatever. If they really fire you for something like that,

229
00:18:17,900 --> 00:18:20,800
there's no point in staying there.

230
00:18:25,095 --> 00:18:29,515
Do you think I can be a proper designer?

231
00:18:31,400 --> 00:18:37,600
Do you think a designer should lie to flatter others?

232
00:18:42,200 --> 00:18:46,400
They say that the workplace is vile. Now I get it.

233
00:18:46,400 --> 00:18:49,900
It's not all about working hard.

234
00:18:49,900 --> 00:18:54,100
What is done is done. We did nothing wrong.

235
00:18:54,100 --> 00:18:56,800
Just be casual like nothing happened.

236
00:18:56,800 --> 00:19:00,000
If they fire you, get another job.

237
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:04,500
Chongqing is full of design companies. Do we have to work there?

238
00:19:04,500 --> 00:19:07,700
I can always sell cakes and support you.

239
00:19:09,700 --> 00:19:12,800
- Thank you, Madam. 
 - Come on. Let's go.

240
00:19:12,800 --> 00:19:15,100
