00:20:17,700 --> 00:20:22,800
Look, I'll show you three apartments. All of them are studios.

256
00:20:22,800 --> 00:20:27,000
One of them has just been renovated and is being rented for the first time.

257
00:20:27,000 --> 00:20:31,200
Under one condition. The landlord wants a six-month payment.

258
00:20:33,100 --> 00:20:35,300
Six-month?

259
00:20:35,300 --> 00:20:38,600
Let's see it first and discuss it later.

260
00:20:38,600 --> 00:20:42,200
All three of them are fine. Everything is ready.

261
00:20:42,200 --> 00:20:44,700
It's perfect for couples like you.

262
00:20:44,700 --> 00:20:47,700
I live nearby. He'll be living alone.

263
00:20:48,800 --> 00:20:53,400
That's even better. The king-size bed will be super cozy.

264
00:20:53,400 --> 00:20:55,600
- Let's take a look. 
 - Let's go.

265
00:20:55,600 --> 00:20:57,600
- Okay. 
 - Let's go.

266
00:21:07,800 --> 00:21:13,800
It was too dark inside. We need the light on during the day.

267
00:21:13,800 --> 00:21:18,400
Miss, apartments with great sunshine are costly in Chongqing.

268
00:21:18,400 --> 00:21:22,700
It's hard to find something like that with your budget.

269
00:21:22,700 --> 00:21:25,400
But it's okay. Let's try the next one.

270
00:21:25,400 --> 00:21:29,600
That one is much brighter and it's nearby.

271
00:21:29,600 --> 00:21:33,300
Shall we just visit the renovated one?

272
00:21:33,300 --> 00:21:34,700
Let's see both.

273
00:21:34,700 --> 00:21:35,900
- Yeah. 
 - Okay.

274
00:21:35,900 --> 00:21:38,440
You could use some options.

275
00:21:38,440 --> 00:21:40,200
This way.

276
00:21:44,795 --> 00:21:47,495
Come on in.

277
00:21:49,200 --> 00:21:51,800
Here's the kitchen, the living room.

278
00:21:51,800 --> 00:21:54,600
The balcony and here's the bedroom.

279
00:21:54,600 --> 00:21:56,100
Take a look inside.

280
00:21:56,100 --> 00:21:59,100
Here's the bathroom.

281
00:22:00,855 --> 00:22:03,095
It's quite big.

282
00:22:04,200 --> 00:22:06,500
This is the bedroom.

283
00:22:11,900 --> 00:22:14,000
The renovation looks nice.

284
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:16,700
It's well-designed and very neat.

285
00:22:16,700 --> 00:22:18,400
This is not bad.

286
00:22:18,400 --> 00:22:21,400
And it's much brighter.

287
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:24,400
I'd say this one is the best.

288
00:22:24,400 --> 00:22:27,200
We have people visiting in the next few days.

289
00:22:27,200 --> 00:22:31,700
This place will get rented in no time.

290
00:22:31,700 --> 00:22:35,800
It's a fine place, but the six-month payment is too much.

291
00:22:35,800 --> 00:22:38,600
How about a three-month payment with a one-month deposit?

292
00:22:38,600 --> 00:22:42,600
We're not leaving in just a year.

293
00:22:43,200 --> 00:22:45,100
So you want it, right?

294
00:22:45,100 --> 00:22:47,200
This place is fine.

295
00:22:47,200 --> 00:22:49,800
Okay, let me talk to the landlord.

296
00:22:49,800 --> 00:22:53,300
May I ask what you do for a living?

297
00:22:53,300 --> 00:22:55,300
I work in a design company.

298
00:22:55,300 --> 00:22:58,900
A designer? Impressive.

299
00:22:58,900 --> 00:23:01,700
And your girlfriend is...

300
00:23:01,700 --> 00:23:03,900
I'm...

301
00:23:03,900 --> 00:23:06,200
She's a researcher.

302
00:23:07,050 --> 00:23:12,375
She's working on sustainable development of human bioenergy.

303
00:23:13,710 --> 00:23:18,235
T-That's impressive.

304
00:23:20,190 --> 00:23:22,495
We're getting this one.

305
00:23:22,495 --> 00:23:28,515
All right, I'll contact the landlord. You can pay the deposit if it's settled.

306
00:23:28,515 --> 00:23:31,075
- Okay. 
 - Okay. Look around. I'll contact the landlord.

307
00:23:31,075 --> 00:23:33,695
- Thank you. 
 - No problem.

308
00:23:33,695 --> 00:23:37,615
I make dumplings. "Human bioenergy"?

309
00:23:37,615 --> 00:23:42,155
- We have to eat and obtain energy, don't we? 
 - You're full of nonsense.

310
00:23:42,155 --> 00:23:44,995
- Another one. 
 - Smells nice.

311
00:23:44,995 --> 00:23:47,775
Take me with you when you're looking for houses.

312
00:23:47,775 --> 00:23:50,575
Otherwise, they may scam you because you're young.

313
00:23:50,575 --> 00:23:53,435
I'll check the contracts and title deeds for you.

314
00:23:53,435 --> 00:23:56,055
Uncle, those are licensed agencies.

315
00:23:56,055 --> 00:23:59,420
Some of them may be frauds, trying to...

316
00:23:59,420 --> 00:24:02,330
Oh no, the soup is coming out.

317
00:24:02,335 --> 00:24:04,595
When are you moving?

318
00:24:04,595 --> 00:24:08,255
If they accept a three-month payment, I can move right away.

319
00:24:08,255 --> 00:24:11,155
You'd better run away from Chen Guangpu.

320
00:24:11,155 --> 00:24:12,895
- Have you tried the cookies? 
 - Yeah.

321
00:24:12,895 --> 00:24:15,175
- Are they good? 
 - Of course.

322
00:24:15,175 --> 00:24:18,955
We should start a pastry. We'll be loaded.

323
00:24:18,955 --> 00:24:21,575
Save it. I'm completely broke.

324
00:24:21,575 --> 00:24:23,675
I don't know what to do with that house.

325
00:24:23,675 --> 00:24:27,455
Just wait. The whole complex is not going to disappear.

326
00:24:27,455 --> 00:24:31,775
Listen, once someone takes over, you'll get the apartment and pay the mortgage.

327
00:24:31,775 --> 00:24:34,695
Be grateful. Isn't it easier when you don't have a mortgage?

328
00:24:34,695 --> 00:24:37,795
- Weird logic. 
 - You know I'm right.

329
00:24:40,550 --> 00:24:43,655
- Leave it. It's bad for digestion. 
 - It's okay.

330
00:24:43,655 --> 00:24:46,215
That's me. Who is it?

331
00:24:46,870 --> 00:24:49,055
Tomorrow morning? Okay.

332
00:24:49,055 --> 00:24:54,195
Contract. ID. Hukou registration. Yeah, I got them.

333
00:24:54,195 --> 00:24:56,315
All right, thank you so much.

334
00:24:56,315 --> 00:25:00,055
- What's wrong? 
 - Dad, the real estate company called.

335
00:25:00,055 --> 00:25:05,275
A company took over the complex to build serviced apartments. We can get our money back.

336
00:25:05,275 --> 00:25:06,955
- We can? Really? 
 - Yeah.

337
00:25:06,955 --> 00:25:08,815
- That's great! 
 - That's great.

338
00:25:08,815 --> 00:25:10,775
I thought there was no hope.

339
00:25:10,775 --> 00:25:15,115
And they suddenly called us. You brought luck by just mentioning it.

340
00:25:15,115 --> 00:25:17,455
- I should talk more. 
 - Wait, wait.

341
00:25:17,455 --> 00:25:19,675
They're giving us cash, right?

342
00:25:19,675 --> 00:25:21,475
Yeah.

343
00:25:21,475 --> 00:25:24,835
But someone took over the complex. Should we just keep the house?

344
00:25:24,835 --> 00:25:28,495
No, Godfather. It's unbuilt. Who knows what's going to happen?

345
00:25:28,495 --> 00:25:31,915
Get the money back. You can get a ready-built house.

346
00:25:31,915 --> 00:25:35,335
- Get the money back first. 
 - Yeah, get the cash.

347
00:25:35,335 --> 00:25:37,835
Yeah, get the cash.

348
00:25:37,835 --> 00:25:40,415
Xiao Que, I'll go with you tomorrow.

349
00:25:40,415 --> 00:25:44,915
No need. You have work. I can go alone. I'll call you if I need you.

350
00:25:44,915 --> 00:25:50,995
All right, this is great news. Shall we celebrate a bit?

351
00:25:50,995 --> 00:25:54,675
- Want a drink? 
 - Come on. Don't encourage him. It's not allowed.

352
00:25:54,675 --> 00:25:57,535
Fine. Just dig in.

353
00:25:57,535 --> 00:26:01,175
Uncle, let's toast with soup. It's just the same.

354
00:26:01,175 --> 00:26:05,755
- Yeah. 
 - Godfather, cheers.  
  -  Cheers. 

355
00:26:05,755 --> 00:26:07,664
Cheers.

356
00:26:17,390 --> 00:26:19,795
You scared me. What's wrong?

357
00:26:19,795 --> 00:26:21,955
There's a new restaurant.

358
00:26:21,955 --> 00:26:25,580
They offer a discount and free drinks. Let's order together.

359
00:26:25,580 --> 00:26:28,005
All right, then.

360
00:26:28,005 --> 00:26:30,705
Why are you so nervous?

361
00:26:30,705 --> 00:26:35,135
I'm so scared that someone may get me to their offices.

362
00:26:35,135 --> 00:26:37,255
You're scared you'd be fired?

363
00:26:37,255 --> 00:26:39,675
I won't even make it through the probation.

364
00:26:39,675 --> 00:26:44,115
But you have to. Then you can get compensation for being fired.

365
00:26:44,115 --> 00:26:48,415
Actually, the probation period is only three months. It's six months on rare occasions.

366
00:26:48,415 --> 00:26:51,175
Three months? So it's almost due.

367
00:26:51,175 --> 00:26:53,635
Yeah, that's right.

368
00:26:54,170 --> 00:26:57,415
I'm just about to rent a place.

369
00:26:58,120 --> 00:27:01,575
Don't be so pessimistic. Nobody's telling you to leave yet.

370
00:27:01,575 --> 00:27:04,375
You're safe as long as Director Wei wants you.

371
00:27:04,950 --> 00:27:07,635
Does he though?

372
00:27:07,635 --> 00:27:10,715
He hasn't told you to leave yet.

373
00:27:10,715 --> 00:27:14,735
Anyway, stay quiet and work harder. Who knows?

374
00:27:18,370 --> 00:27:21,075
Which restaurant? Lunch is on me.

375
00:27:26,090 --> 00:27:28,620
- I got the money back. Guess how much. 
 - How much?

376
00:27:28,620 --> 00:27:32,175
Eight hundred grand! I feel so rich now!

377
00:27:32,175 --> 00:27:34,015
Keep it down, silly.

378
00:27:34,015 --> 00:27:36,635
I'm not silly. I have 800 grand.

379
00:27:36,635 --> 00:27:39,915
I thought we were doomed and we couldn't get the money back.

380
00:27:39,915 --> 00:27:42,755
Now that I have the money, it's like winning the lottery.

381
00:27:42,755 --> 00:27:46,495
It's your money in the first place. You actually lost interest.

382
00:27:46,495 --> 00:27:49,315
I don't care. It feels like winning a lottery.

383
00:27:49,315 --> 00:27:51,095
I wired you the surgery fee.

384
00:27:51,095 --> 00:27:52,175
No need.

385
00:27:52,175 --> 00:27:55,435
I have to give you my dad's surgery fee.

386
00:27:55,435 --> 00:27:57,195
You can pay for my surgery.

387
00:27:57,195 --> 00:27:59,915
Nonsense. There is no surgery.

388
00:27:59,915 --> 00:28:02,555
The rich lady is taking you to lunch.

389
00:28:02,555 --> 00:28:03,975
I already had lunch.

390
00:28:03,975 --> 00:28:06,975
So early?

391
00:28:06,975 --> 00:28:10,575
Huang Xiaolu wanted to order takeout so I joined her.

392
00:28:10,575 --> 00:28:12,795
You did?

393
00:28:12,795 --> 00:28:14,455
It was my treat.

394
00:28:14,455 --> 00:28:19,030
You're already buying her lunch?

395
00:28:19,030 --> 00:28:22,495
She's the only one who speaks to me now.

396
00:28:22,495 --> 00:28:24,355
We're brothers in hardship.

397
00:28:24,355 --> 00:28:26,675
Right, the agency called me.

398
00:28:26,675 --> 00:28:29,555
The landlord agreed. I can sign the contract and move in.

399
00:28:29,555 --> 00:28:33,655
All right, let's sign the contract. After that, we can get some furniture.

400
00:28:33,655 --> 00:28:37,400
All right, you already sound like a rich person.

401
00:28:37,400 --> 00:28:39,275
That's right.

402
00:28:39,275 --> 00:28:41,415
So generous.

403
00:28:49,310 --> 00:28:51,675
- Like a boss lady. 
 - This way, please.

404
00:28:51,675 --> 00:28:53,235
- Wave the flag. 
 - This way.

405
00:28:53,235 --> 00:28:55,935
Come here. Be seated.

406
00:28:55,935 --> 00:28:59,635
Make yourself at home. Don't be shy.

407
00:28:59,635 --> 00:29:06,275
Get whatever you want. Pile up the plates.

408
00:29:06,275 --> 00:29:07,835
Here.

409
00:29:07,835 --> 00:29:13,235
We know that you got your money back. But you're acting like you suddenly got rich.

410
00:29:13,235 --> 00:29:18,015
Xiao Que, will you join me for investment?

411
00:29:18,015 --> 00:29:22,835
That's the only way to make big money. It's not a good deal to get interest from a bank.

412
00:29:22,835 --> 00:29:27,115
Your stocks and funds are glowing green. We don't have the money for that.

413
00:29:27,115 --> 00:29:31,875
- My... 
 - It suits him on the head. So green.

414
00:29:31,875 --> 00:29:36,795
Don't pretend that you're better when you get drunk, crying every day.

415
00:29:36,795 --> 00:29:39,595
- I... 
 - Keep drinking.

416
00:29:39,595 --> 00:29:41,995
Place the order. The drink is ending.

417
00:29:41,995 --> 00:29:45,075
I have to move some things to the new apartment.

418
00:29:45,075 --> 00:29:46,675
Already?

419
00:29:46,675 --> 00:29:47,995
Tonight?

420
00:29:47,995 --> 00:29:49,955
We signed the contract.

421
00:29:50,730 --> 00:29:53,395
Don't you have a conscience? For this woman...

422
00:29:53,395 --> 00:29:56,295
- What about it? What about it? 
 - What about it?

423
00:29:56,295 --> 00:29:58,515
What about it?

424
00:30:01,870 --> 00:30:04,735
- Get everything. Get anything you like. 
 - This. Sliced beef.

425
00:30:04,735 --> 00:30:07,815
My parents came. They're almost home.

426
00:30:07,815 --> 00:30:11,215
- Are you going to eat? 
 - Of course not. I have to pack up.

427
00:30:11,215 --> 00:30:12,615
My things are there.

428
00:30:12,615 --> 00:30:14,275
I'll pack up my trash.

429
00:30:14,275 --> 00:30:15,855
What trash?

430
00:30:15,855 --> 00:30:18,415
We'll wait for you. Hurry.

431
00:30:18,415 --> 00:30:19,955
- Let's eat. 
 - Place the order.

432
00:30:19,955 --> 00:30:22,555
- Tripes. 
 - Yes.

433
00:30:38,670 --> 00:30:42,275
Mom, Dad, why did you come?

434
00:30:42,275 --> 00:30:46,015
Why didn't you tell me? I could have picked you up.

435
00:30:46,015 --> 00:30:49,035
If we had told you,

436
00:30:49,035 --> 00:30:52,575
how would we find out about your brilliant lifestyle?

437
00:30:52,575 --> 00:30:53,995
W-What?

438
00:30:53,995 --> 00:30:57,035
Son, you like wearing this?

439
00:30:57,035 --> 00:31:02,395
No, Mom. It's Lin Tuo's.

440
00:31:02,395 --> 00:31:04,155
Remember Lin Tuo? You've met him.

441
00:31:04,155 --> 00:31:07,035
He's taller than me. Very handsome.

442
00:31:07,035 --> 00:31:10,935
He got his girlfriend a birthday gift and left it here.

443
00:31:10,935 --> 00:31:14,755
Chen Guangpu, you're a grown-up and a graduate.

444
00:31:14,755 --> 00:31:17,315
Stop messing around!

445
00:31:17,315 --> 00:31:22,815
Your mom and I work hard to make money. And you're messing around?

446
00:31:22,815 --> 00:31:25,695
Who do you think you are?

447
00:31:25,695 --> 00:31:30,675
What's this? Yuetian Entertainment?

448
00:31:30,675 --> 00:31:32,515
You're visiting that kind of place?

449
00:31:32,515 --> 00:31:36,735
No, Dad. It's just an ordinary KTV, not the ones you visit.

450
00:31:36,735 --> 00:31:38,395
What?

451
00:31:38,395 --> 00:31:43,415
Mom, it's just an ordinary KTV. That's where we go. Both of us.

452
00:31:43,415 --> 00:31:45,095
It's like a restaurant, right?

453
00:31:45,095 --> 00:31:49,355
Yeah, KTV. I only go to Zhao's. You know him, right?

454
00:31:49,355 --> 00:31:55,015
Like father, like son. You're just the same.

455
00:31:55,015 --> 00:31:58,875
I'll get back to you.

456
00:31:58,875 --> 00:32:02,495
Just you wait. Step aside.

457
00:32:03,130 --> 00:32:06,575
Honey.

458
00:32:12,590 --> 00:32:17,795
 High pressure 149 mmHg. Low pressure 102 mmHg. 

459
00:32:17,795 --> 00:32:20,655
 Pulse. Eighty-two per minute. 

460
00:32:20,655 --> 00:32:23,175
Why is it a bit high today?

461
00:32:23,175 --> 00:32:24,675
Did you skip the pills?

462
00:32:24,675 --> 00:32:26,635
I didn't sleep well.

463
00:32:26,635 --> 00:32:30,415
Dad, I've been thinking about the house.

464
00:32:30,415 --> 00:32:36,995
The money we have can only cover the down payment of something in the suburbs.

465
00:32:36,995 --> 00:32:42,295
So we can look for second-hand houses.

466
00:32:42,295 --> 00:32:44,535
I've been waiting to talk to you.

467
00:32:44,535 --> 00:32:48,295
I kind of changed my mind about it.

468
00:32:48,295 --> 00:32:53,255
What's wrong? You got scared because of what had happened?

469
00:32:53,255 --> 00:32:56,435
Not really. I've been thinking.

470
00:32:56,435 --> 00:32:59,955
You're working so hard to get money.

471
00:32:59,955 --> 00:33:04,635
And I'm working nonstop. I don't mind living frugally.

472
00:33:04,635 --> 00:33:09,055
But my pretty and sweet girl can barely afford some nice clothes.

473
00:33:09,055 --> 00:33:11,135
I see how He Xindi is dressed.

474
00:33:11,135 --> 00:33:15,355
It makes me upset to see you in such plain clothes.

475
00:33:15,355 --> 00:33:17,475
It didn't even cross my mind.

476
00:33:17,475 --> 00:33:21,995
Seriously. Dad is not a money-maker.

477
00:33:21,995 --> 00:33:28,615
Look at me. And Xiao Lin paid for my surgery, right?

478
00:33:31,670 --> 00:33:38,480
I just don't want you to do odd jobs, make dumplings,

479
00:33:38,480 --> 00:33:42,475
or suffer just for some petty money.

480
00:33:42,475 --> 00:33:44,395
I'm not suffering.

481
00:33:44,395 --> 00:33:48,455
That's it. I've made up my mind.

482
00:33:48,455 --> 00:33:52,115
We're not going to get a loan again.

483
00:33:52,115 --> 00:33:56,135
Right? And you're a lady now.

484
00:33:56,135 --> 00:33:59,395
You'll get married with Xiao Lin sooner or later, right?

485
00:33:59,395 --> 00:34:02,215
You'll move out once you get married.

486
00:34:02,215 --> 00:34:04,535
You'll have your own place.

487
00:34:04,535 --> 00:34:07,575
I can't live in a giant house by myself.

488
00:34:07,575 --> 00:34:12,594
Dad, I just can't let you live in an old house without an elevator.

489
00:34:13,890 --> 00:34:17,415
We're on the second floor. Why do we need an elevator?

490
00:34:17,415 --> 00:34:23,180
Besides, I may have some minor problems, but I can easily climb 12 floors, let alone two.

491
00:34:23,180 --> 00:34:27,295
Besides, climbing stairs is a great exercise for me.

492
00:34:29,355 --> 00:34:33,734
Come on, I know you're a sweet girl.

493
00:34:33,734 --> 00:34:37,915
But listen to me, okay?

494
00:34:37,915 --> 00:34:43,320
We've been saving up for quite a while.

495
00:34:43,320 --> 00:34:46,960
It's time to plan for your future.

496
00:34:46,960 --> 00:34:51,180
I can't possibly use so much money.

497
00:34:51,960 --> 00:34:57,515
Don't you want to open a store to sell coffee and cakes?

498
00:34:57,515 --> 00:35:00,395
Are you telling me to open a store?

499
00:35:00,395 --> 00:35:06,355
Do it. It can be your career. Isn't it trendy? Start your business.

500
00:35:06,355 --> 00:35:10,315
And you like it. Isn't that wonderful?

501
00:35:10,315 --> 00:35:12,615
What if I lose money?

502
00:35:12,615 --> 00:35:16,495
Then we'll save up again.

503
00:35:16,495 --> 00:35:20,375
It's not like we can't make money.

504
00:35:23,575 --> 00:35:25,575
Miss An Zhique.

505
00:35:25,575 --> 00:35:30,795
